snippet.description:

#AmberHeardQuotes





The Quotes
1 - You Can’t Respect Yourself If You’re Afraid To Be Who You Are - Amber Heard
2 - All I’ve ever needed is myself
3 - I am just like any other girl, a sucker for romance
4 - I’ve always been a private person, and I’ve always valued my private life
5 - It requires bravery to do something no one else around you is doing
6 - I don’t label myself one way or another. I love who I love; it’s the person that matters
7 - It’s rare to have even half-meaningful conversations in the film industry
8 - I think my mother realized she had a somewhat unusual daughter pretty early on
9 - I am a firm believer that you can have the body you want, only to the extent that you’re willing to work for it
10 - It’s my job in Hollywood to find roles where I get to be a character, not a bathing suit
11 - I have always been very rebellious and gone against the grain. I’ve always challenged the standards set before me
12 - Once you start working out, you feel better and it becomes something you make time to do
13 - I love my horror films and they will always be very close to me
14 - I personally think that if you deny something or if you hide something you’re inadvertently admitting it’s wrong
15 - Everybody enjoys when a woman is her own character in a movie or otherwise
16 - I can sit in front of the TV and watch an old romantic film and be transfixed
17 - Young women from a very young age are taught that life will be easier if you can just turn on the charming smile and say very little and be complacent and docile and sweet
18 - Reading keeps me sane. Growing up, it was my escape, my alternative; it provided both rebellion and peace
19 - School was a waste of time for me. I was bored and left at 16. I started taking correspondence courses at college instead. I did incredibly well. I won an award for my grades
